<div id="review_322769762" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/322769762" />
    <a title="M." class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/5157049-m"><img alt="M." src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1618013068p2/5157049.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/322769762?book_show_action=true">May 02, 2012</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="M." class="user" itemprop="url" name="M." href="/user/show/5157049-m">M.</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9789500305884" href="/book/show/13631343-don-juan">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5157049-m?shelf=favorite-books">favorite-books</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5157049-m?shelf=france">france</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5157049-m?shelf=play">play</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5157049-m?shelf=comedy">comedy</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer322769762" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3942244437770149470">Timeless. Many of the things, if not all of them are very actual for a book way ahead of its time, and it&apos;s something logical for a book that is about human nature. But it&apos;s always done in that unique and humorous way that Molière has. Above all, it allows us to laugh at our own attitudes and that&apos;s something to consider, but we shouldn&apos;t forget the moral effect that is way too overlooked in today&apos;s parodies. <br/><br/>As a great fan of Molière&apos;s work this comedy hasn&apos;t disappointed me at all. Very recome</span>
  <span id="freeText3942244437770149470" style="display:none">Timeless. Many of the things, if not all of them are very actual for a book way ahead of its time, and it's something logical for a book that is about human nature. But it's always done in that unique and humorous way that Molière has. Above all, it allows us to laugh at our own attitudes and that's something to consider, but we shouldn't forget the moral effect that is way too overlooked in today's parodies. <br /><br />As a great fan of Molière's work this comedy hasn't disappointed me at all. Very recomendable.</span>
  <a data-text-id="3942244437770149470" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
