<div id="review_193316842" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/193316842" />
    <a title="Jenna Fresco" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/5941924-jenna-fresco"><img alt="Jenna Fresco" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/f_50x66-6a03a5c12233c941481992b82eea8d23.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/193316842?book_show_action=true">Aug 02, 2011</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Jenna Fresco" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Jenna Fresco" href="/user/show/5941924-jenna-fresco">Jenna Fresco</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer193316842" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7409113198199263627">Don Juan is one of the more lush, well-written plays I&apos;ve read. The acts and scenes are not set up as with many other plays; the scenes are all very short. The interactions between Don Juan and his valet are comical and so well staged. Don Juan, an amusingly devious character, seems shallow through his actions, but he holds a certain complexity. One must wonder why he is what he is. Though he&apos;s destined to meet his downfall, I can&apos;t help up love the wittiness of his character.</span>
  <span id="freeText7409113198199263627" style="display:none">Don Juan is one of the more lush, well-written plays I've read. The acts and scenes are not set up as with many other plays; the scenes are all very short. The interactions between Don Juan and his valet are comical and so well staged. Don Juan, an amusingly devious character, seems shallow through his actions, but he holds a certain complexity. One must wonder why he is what he is. Though he's destined to meet his downfall, I can't help up love the wittiness of his character.</span>
  <a data-text-id="7409113198199263627" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


