<div id="review_236235369" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/236235369" />
    <a title="Bogdan" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1679953-bogdan"><img alt="Bogdan" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1364230014p2/1679953.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/236235369?book_show_action=true">Nov 16, 2011</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Bogdan" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Bogdan" href="/user/show/1679953-bogdan">Bogdan</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1679953-bogdan?shelf=theatrum-mundi">theatrum-mundi</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer236235369" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8809331023968925026">&quot;Life is a theatre&quot; says Don Juan somewhere towards the end of the play, and I totally agree it. This is one of the few ate from Moliere that it is not a comedy and also do not have a happy ending. This is natural according to the believes of the time when the play was written, that required a strict moral behavior. Nowadays, this is changed and Don Juan type is not anymore uncommon.<br/>My copy of this book is in Romanian.</span>
  <span id="freeText8809331023968925026" style="display:none">"Life is a theatre" says Don Juan somewhere towards the end of the play, and I totally agree it. This is one of the few ate from Moliere that it is not a comedy and also do not have a happy ending. This is natural according to the believes of the time when the play was written, that required a strict moral behavior. Nowadays, this is changed and Don Juan type is not anymore uncommon.<br />My copy of this book is in Romanian.</span>
